pokedexEntries.red: It uses its whiskers to maintain its balance. It apparently slows down if they are cut off.
pokedexEntries.blue: It uses its whiskers to maintain its balance. It apparently slows down if they are cut off.
pokedexEntries.yellow: Its hind feet are webbed. They act as flippers, so it can swim in rivers and hunt for prey.
pokedexEntries.gold: Gnaws on anything with its tough fangs. It can even topple concrete buildings by gnawing on them.
pokedexEntries.silver: Its whiskers help it to maintain balance. Its fangs never stop growing, so it gnaws to pare them down.
pokedexEntries.crystal: The webs on its hind legs enable it to cross rivers. It searches wide areas for food.
pokedexEntries.ruby: Raticate's sturdy fangs grow steadily. To keep them ground down, it gnaws on rocks and logs. It may even chew on the walls of houses.
pokedexEntries.sapphire: Raticate's sturdy fangs grow steadily. To keep them ground down, it gnaws on rocks and logs. It may even chew on the walls of houses.
pokedexEntries.emerald: A Raticate's sturdy fangs grow steadily. To keep them ground down, it gnaws on rocks and logs. It may even chew on the walls of houses.
pokedexEntries.fireRed: Its rear feet have three toes each. They are webbed, enabling it to swim across rivers.
pokedexEntries.leafGreen: It uses its whiskers to maintain its balance. It apparently slows down if they are cut off.
pokedexEntries.diamond: It whittles its constantly growing fangs by gnawing on hard things. It can chew apart cinder walls.

pokedexEntries.white: It whittles its constantly growing fangs by gnawing on hard things. It can chew apart cinder walls.
pokedexEntries.black2: With its long fangs, this surprisingly violent Pokémon can gnaw away even thick concrete with ease.

pokedexEntries.y: The webs on its hind legs enable it to cross rivers. It searches wide areas for food.
pokedexEntries.omegaRuby: Raticate’s sturdy fangs grow steadily. To keep them ground down, it gnaws on rocks and logs. It may even chew on the walls of houses.
pokedexEntries.alphaSapphire: Raticate’s sturdy fangs grow steadily. To keep them ground down, it gnaws on rocks and logs. It may even chew on the walls of houses.
pokedexEntries.sun: Its hind feet are webbed, so it's a strong swimmer. It can cross rivers and sometimes even oceans.
pokedexEntries.moon: Its disposition is far more violent than its looks would suggest. Don't let your hand get too close to its face, as it could bite your hand clean off.
pokedexEntries.ultraSun: People say that it fled from its enemies by using its small webbed hind feet to swim from island to island in Alola.
pokedexEntries.ultraMoon: Its whiskers are essential for maintaining its balance. No matter how friendly you are, it will get angry and bite you if you touch its whiskers.
